      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 47
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD is an investment-grade example of the final-generation rotary icon. At its heart is the 13B-REW twin-rotor engine, featuring a meticulously maintained sequential twin-turbocharger system that provides a seamless transition and robust boost pressure across the rev range. The chassis maintains its legendary 50/50 weight distribution, supported by a factory-spec four-wheel double-wishbone suspension and a Torsen limited-slip differential for neutral cornering dynamics. Recent mechanical stewardship includes a full silicone vacuum line overhaul, a high-capacity aluminum radiator to manage thermal loads, and verified compression results that exceed factory baseline. The five-speed manual transmission offers crisp engagement with no synchro wear. This specimen is free of the typical dash warping or thermal degradation, representing a rare opportunity to own a mechanically uncompromising FD in its purest form.",
      "price": 46500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
